        {q:"The 'director' of a play is responsible for:",o:["Selling tickets","Overall artistic vision and guiding actors","Playing the music","Building the set"],a:"Overall artistic vision and guiding actors",e:"They interpret the script and coordinate the production."},
        {q:"The 'E.T. Mensah' is considered the:",o:["King of Kpanlogo","King of Highlife","Father of Hiplife","Master of Adowa"],a:"King of Highlife",e:"His band 'The Tempos' defined the Highlife golden age."},
        {q:"The 'clay' used for pottery is shaped on a:",o:["Lathe","Potter's wheel or by hand","Loom","Easel"],a:"Potter's wheel or by hand",e:"The wheel spins the clay while the potter molds it."},
        {q:"The 'costume' in a theatre performance helps to:",o:["Sell snacks","Indicate character, status, and period","Light the stage","Record the show"],a:"Indicate character, status, and period",e:"It is a vital visual design element."},
        {q:"The 'Akan' goldweights (Abrammuo) were used for:",o:["Decoration only","Weighing gold dust for trade","Fishing","Building"],a:"Weighing gold dust for trade",e:"They were intricately cast in miniature figurative forms."},
        {q:"The 'harmony' in visual art is achieved when:",o:["Colors clash","Elements are in chaos","All parts of the design work together","There is no focal point"],a:"All parts of the design work together",e:"It creates a sense of completeness."},
        {q:"The 'Kete' drum ensemble features:",o:["Only one drum","A set of tuned drums played with sticks and hands","Flutes only","Xylophones only"],a:"A set of tuned drums played with sticks and hands",e:"Complex polyrhythms characterize the ensemble."},
        {q:"The 'Mona Lisa' was painted using which medium?",o:["Acrylic","Watercolor","Oil paint","Fresco"],a:"Oil paint",e:"Leonardo used the sfumato technique in oils."},
        {q:"The 'relief' sculpture means the forms project:",o:["Inward","From a flat background","Only in the air","Underground"],a:"From a flat background",e:"High relief projects deeply; low relief is shallow."},
        {q:"The 'caller' in traditional singing leads the:",o:["Drumming","Response from the crowd","Dance","Costume"],a:"Response from the crowd",e:"Call and Response is a key African musical element."},
        {q:"The 'canvas' is a common surface for:",o:["Sculpture","Painting (Acrylic/Oil)","Knitting","Pottery"],a:"Painting (Acrylic/Oil)",e:"It is stretched onto wooden frames."},
        {q:"The 'Atumpan' drums are considered:",o:["Children's toys","Talking drums for communication","Foreign instruments","Water jugs"],a:"Talking drums for communication",e:"They mimic the tonal language of the Akan."},
        {q:"The 'color' black in Akan symbolism often represents:",o:["Peace","Mourning, maturity, and spiritual energy","Joy","Harvest"],a:"Mourning, maturity, and spiritual energy",e:"Adinkra black is serious and protective."},
        {q:"The 'script' in theatre provides the:",o:["Tickets","Dialogues and stage directions","Food","Costume"],a:"Dialogues and stage directions",e:"It is the written blueprint of the play."}
